works with.  During his few years at the company he has gotten several promotions and afew pay increases due to his hard work and dedication.  He is up for another promotion in a month - supervisor of the department he works for.  Enter a woman - not nearly has hard working, somewhat of a loudmouth, and rather bossy.  She has been in the company for many years, with only lateral movement in the company.  She too is up for the same promotion.  One fateful day she learns who her competition is, and upon gathing up info on the guy - she can pretty much figure out he's a shoe-in for the position.  What does she do?  Waves the good ol flag of sexual harrasment.  The quiet, mild mannered guy -who had seen this woman about, knew she never did any work, and was pretty much a blabber mouth - is asked to leave the company with no explination of his side of the story.  No witnessess - just her word against his.  Yes it's a real story - and how do I know the guy is quiet and well mannered - because he is my brother.<br><br>Now what if it was my brother who went to his boss saying that this woman was a complete slacker?  Different ending I'm sure. Now - the analogy - Person A posts a huge flame about person B.  Persons C,D,E,F,G,H,I,J and K all post saying what a complete ass Person A is.  Person L is a friend of Person B, and gets flamed for not only being friends with B, but gets chewed out for trying to defend someone who hasn't even posted yet.  Person B finally posts, and they get chewed out, have their past drug up, and made to feel small and insignificant.<br><br>Now - What if it was Person B comming forth first, complaining about the same incident from a different point of view?<br><br>Just a thought to prove that people are so eager to jump up and lay blame on the &quot;bad guy&quot; when upon viewing either side of the story - the other party involved could be &quot;bad&quot;.  Everybody here had an opinion about the evil's of this and that - when only a handful of people were actually at the event.  A point of view can be a very skewed thing - and only an outsider (with the ability to read tells and group chat) would get the true, clear picture of what happened - and even that would be skewed if they had relations with either of the said parties.  I tend to see this alot on the &quot;Flame&quot; boards.  Yes, this might be the purpose of the boards...but I also see alot of people get verbally ripped apart over simple mistakes, whether they be ingame or here.  Even when posting about a simple issue - people go off like a thunderstorm, bashing down another person for their point of view.  As a great tee-shirt once stated &quot;If opinions were like a$$holes, this place would be an airport.&quot;  We all have them, some of us voice them, some of us keep quiet.  I understand why some people keep quiet.  I know that chances are I will never be able to change another person's point of view. I wouldn't want to either. It is what makes us unique.  But there is no point in destroying somebody because they think differently from you.  People can pull up facts and figures about either side of an issue and be just as right as the opposition.  You are not winning any battles by cursing and belittling people for the way they feel.<br><br>Trains happen, bad pulls happen, misquoted items happen, misinformation happens, getting flamed for not getting rezed or gated happens all the time too. Granted - there are people who cause trains because they are jerks - there are people who do bad pulls in the hopes of killing people off at zonelines.  I am NOT defending these people.  I'm not defending the actions of rude people who think they are God's gift to Everquest and you have to bow down and do whatever they ask you to (without Please and Thank You).  There are ALWAYS exceptions to every rule.  But the occasional, accidental mistake does happen, even to the best of players.  If they come back with a sincere apology, can we just forgive and forget?<br><br>Next time somebody comes on the Flames board - can we try to keep in mind they are here to blow off steam - the purpose of the board - and not wip out the pitchforks and flaming torches before we get a clearer picture of what happened?<br><br>I'll probably get flamed for trying to make some semblance of peace - but I'm a cleric - I gotta try.  I'm not being sarcastic - I'm being honest.  I'm not targeting this post any anyone in particular.  Perhaps it's just me that tries to keep in mind that Mothers, Fathers, and children play this game and post on this board.  I wouldn't want to see somebody I loved and cared about getting ripped apart as some poor people do here and in game.<br><br>I guess what brought this up was our recent EQ loss. (I too, lost a family member a meer month before my wedding.) I've read her posts for some time, thought she was a brilliant and insightful person, and then her most recent one caught me by surprise.  Alot of thoughts went through my head, but I never posted.  I'm glad I didn't...since I wouldn't want to sit here regretting what I had wrote with no chance of removing it.  Would you really want somebody's final thought about you being along the lines of &quot;So-and-so is such an a$$&quot;? <p>~Kristallis Holyheart, 53 Vicar, officer of The Kindred Souls<br>~~Wife of Relk Holyheart - brave and noble leader of The Kindred Souls<br><i>~We do not stop playing because we grow old....we grow old because we stop playing.~</i><center><a href="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm"target="_blank"><img src="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/mythresult/unicorn.jpg"border="0" width="330" height="175"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukristallis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kristallis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> 